FBIS4-64241 "drweu084aa_94003" FBIS-WEU-94-084 Daily Report 29 Apr 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS IAEA on DPRK Rejection of Inspection Proposal IAEA on DPRK Rejection of Inspection Proposal AU3004130794 Paris AFP in English 2330 GMT 29 Apr 94 AU3004130794 Paris AFP English BFN [Excerpt] Vienna, April 30 (AFP) -- North Korea has rejected conditions set by the International Atomic Energy Agency [IAEA] for new inspections of its nuclear sites, the IAEA said Friday [29 April]. "The new reply from Pyongyang to our demands, which arrived in Vienna Friday afternoon, is unsatisfactory," said IAEA spokesman Hans-Friedrich Meyer, adding that inspectors would not therefore travel to North Korea this weekend. "We will discuss the situation again with the member states at the start of next week," he said. [passage omitted]
